It seems like a prayer-like couplet. Here's the translation:

Come to me, Lord, and sit down, then my soul will be satisfied; 
Every day, He does new things, and His loving nature is revealed.

Here is the translation:

The fully lit lamp shines much, the temple of understanding made equal to jewels; 
It is seen that people have become wise, it seems as if they have taken many steps with great love.

Here are the translations:

One says to the man who does darshan: "You're crying, your face is saying yes yes; 
The past festivals have filled the granary with much grain."

Here is the translation:

The Master's foot has arrived, I am not worthy to gaze; 
He says, "Take this pair of hands, sit down at Ambadi, you are not worthy."

Here is the translation:

Whatever has been seen by one's eyes, a slave (of senses) has fulfilled it in his mind, and hopes; 
Seated at the chariot of saints, without any effort, a resident of Ayodhya becomes liberal.

Here is the translation:

Take golden color, take those flowers away, and let the one who takes leave; 
Many take away the garland of flowers, and my life hangs on your love.

Questions arise in the north, many questions; 
One knows of the victory of Swami's companions;
In this way, everyone is left behind, showing one's own truth.
